# Fixture FM3: `a`, `true`, `false` are position-sensitive keywords.
#
# Hypothesis: An over-eager keyword scanner may treat `a` as rdf:type in
# non-predicate positions, or `true`/`false` as booleans outside object
# position, producing incorrect parse errors or wrong node types.
#
# Expected: all three statements parse successfully.
#   - `<http://example/s> a <http://example/C>` — `a` in predicate position
#     is rdf:type (valid).
#   - `<http://example/a>` in subject position is an IRI, NOT the keyword.
#   - `true` in object position is the boolean literal
#     "true"^^xsd:boolean (valid).
#
# Divergence signal: AcceptRejectSplit or ObjectMismatch if keyword leaks
# into subject or IRI positions.
#
# Spec: Turtle §2.4; grammar `verb ::= predicate | 'a'`;
#       `object ::= ... | BooleanLiteral`.

<http://example/s> a <http://example/C> .
<http://example/a> <http://example/p> <http://example/o> .
<http://example/s> <http://example/p> true .
<http://example/s> <http://example/p> false .
